All to say, his north star is also mine and I will continue to build alongside him, and Quinn, and our entire team with that goal in mind. This turned into an appreciation post. That wasn't my intention, yet here we are. Love you bro. Thanks for inspiring me. @rpnickson

We were born in Venezuela. On one side of our family, we experienced western privilege. The other side - poverty, disadvantage, how impossible it feels to change your circumstance, how lucky we were to fall on the other side. The guilt of privilege in the face of family, of love.

Reader, this founder is my brother. I have a lucrative job in an industry I mostly love... But in him I see a visionary daring to build a model that will innovate, take advantage of new tech, the underlying mission to reinvent economic inequality.

I spoke to a dear founder yesterday who admitted his exhaustion, how taxing it is to build in this space of innovation, hope, non-stop speed, often cruelty. But he remembered the goal: how we are on the verge of a redistribution of wealth, the great equalizer, his north star.

Every once in a while I stop and wonder how I got to a place in my life where I'm paying thousands of dollars for jpgs... but then I remember I'm investing in brands, companies -- dreams for the future and the people behind them...
